Each implementation uses a unique combination of mathematical operations to compute the priority score for each bin. The base structure involves an exponential term multiplied by the item and the mean of bins, with additional terms using different trigonometric or logarithmic functions to add complexity and uniqueness to each function. This ensures that each implementation is distinct and adheres to the problem constraints.
