1. Place the item in the bin with the least space (smallest bin).
2. Place the item in the bin with the most space (largest bin).
3. Place the item in the bin that would result in the least wasted space.
4. Place the item in the bin with the smallest gap that can still fit the item.
5. Place the item in the bin with the largest gap that can still fit the item.
6. Place the priority based on some combination or weighted average of these factors.
7. Use exponential or other non-linear functions to weight the factors.

